ONITSHA – Defend Your Right Foundation is a human rights group poised to help ordinary Nigerians to know, enjoy and defend their rights which its emphasis is on knowledge and training of their members each second and last Sundays of every Month. According to the foundation, this is to build a capacity and personal development. Capitalizing on the theme of her last year’s paralegal training which which was captioned: MOVING FROM HUMAN RIGHTS TO HUMAN LIFE, the group realized that they cannot continue to use old methods to solve new problems. Okorocha Declares For Presidency, Pledges To Surpass Buhari In… Delta: Keston Okoro Dumps PDP For APC Disclosing this to Newsmen after in Onitsha the chairman of the Foundation, Mr Charles Ejefonye, who anchored the training, noted that, the group must be repositioned in order to meet the challenges of 2022 .A said a lot of challenges affecting human rights and human life were identified .These include but not limited to: kidnapping, touting, extortions by government agencies, abuse of various forms, cultism, ritualism, rape, gender based violence e.t.c, he pointed. Ejefeonye who cited Anambra State as a case study, noted that the group resolved to place more demand, mount more pressure and hold the incoming administration of Prof Soludo responsible and accountable for any human rights violation from State agents. In his word, “The group will also help the government in bringing to her knowledge and attention the various forms of abuses taking place in the state.” Ejefeonye urged Nigerians to equip themselves with knowledge since it’s a truism that KNOWLEDGE IS POWER.